{
  "texts": [
    "In wastewater treatment, AI optimizes processes to enhance pollutant removal and reduce energy consumption; machine learning algorithms, for example, optimize incineration processes at treatment plants to achieve significant energy savings (Xu et al., 2024).",
    "Mechanisms for enhancing resilience AI interventions significantly enhance climate risk management, adaptability, and resilience in the water resources sector through several concrete mechanisms.",
    "Enhanced predictive modeling enables proactive planning by forecasting rainfall patterns, streamflow, and groundwater recharge under various climate change scenarios (Banerjee et al., 2024).",
    "These AI-driven models support timely resource allocation and are recommended for climate adaptation efforts in places like Kigali, Rwanda (Banerjee et al., 2024; Bizimana et al., 2024; Kartal, 2024).",
    "Data-driven decision support systems further empower water management strategies by integrating diverse data sources (Heo et al., 2024)."
  ]
}